# Naming

All project identifiers must be **English**.

## Forbidden

- Russian letters in names
- Transliteration of Russian words (`Zakaz`, `Klient`, `Masterskaya`, `Priemka`, …)

Applies to:

- file and directory names
- namespaces, classes, interfaces, traits, enums
- methods, functions, properties, constants, parameters
- DB tables/columns when introducing new schema in this refactor
- test names and factory/seeder identifiers

## Allowed

- English domain terms: `Order`, `OrderItem`, `Reception`, `Workshop`, `Estimate`
- User-facing copy / comments / docs may be Russian
- String literals for UI/API messages may be Russian when that is product copy

```php
// ❌ BAD
class Zakaz {}
public function sozdatPriemku(): void {}
private string $orientirovochnayaStoimost;

// ✅ GOOD
class Order {}
public function completeReception(): void {}
private string $estimatedCost;
```
